    {
      "text": "[PRINT] Print-in-place three-start spiral fidget — print flat on the base, NO supports, NO raft. Use thin layers (0.12-0.16 mm) and 100% part cooling so each spiral solidifies before the next layer is laid down; thick layers or weak cooling let adjacent blades bond. 3-4 walls, 15-20% infill, PLA. After printing, give it a firm first twist to free the blades — they screw apart. If the blades fuse: raise the Print clearance parameter, lower Spiral turns (steeper helix prints cleaner), or enlarge the Central bore. componentCount === 3 (one per arm).",
